---
name: Art Direction
description: >
  If multiple versions of an image are desired _not_ simply for resolution
  switching but also for art direction, use a `<picture>` element with
  multiple `<source>` elements therein.
  More info [here](http://blog.cloudfour.com/a-framework-for-discussing-responsive-images-solutions/#artdirection)
  and [here](http://www.smashingmagazine.com/2014/05/14/responsive-images-done-right-guide-picture-srcset/).
  Relies on [Picturefill](http://scottjehl.github.io/picturefill/) for
  [certain browsers](http://caniuse.com/#feat=picture).
---

<picture class="demo-responsive-img">
  {{! use this image for breakpoints over 40em }}
  <source
    media="(min-width: 40em)"
    srcset="/images/fpo/business-2x.jpg 1920w,
            /images/fpo/business.jpg 960w"
    sizes="960px"> {{! cap these out at 960px wide }}
  {{! otherwise, use this one }}
  <source
    srcset="/images/fpo/business-crop-2x.jpg 640w,
            /images/fpo/business-crop.jpg 320w"
    sizes="100vw"> {{! fill viewport width }}
  {{! fallback image }}
  <img src="/images/fpo/business.jpg" alt="stock photos FTW">
</picture>
